TY  - JOUR
AB  - [We provide a result on prospect theory decision makers who are na&#xef;ve about the time inconsistency induced by probability weighting. If a market offers a sufficiently rich set of investment strategies, investors postpone their trading decisions indefinitely due to a strong preference for skewness. We conclude that probability weighting in combination with na&#xef;vet&#xe9; leads to unrealistic predictions for a wide range of dynamic setups.]
